cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on planning for Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs) in unstructured environments. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Truncated Signed Distance Fields (TSDFs), a common implicit surface representation used in computer vision. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as TSDFs are also used in computer graphics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of trajectory optimization methods, which can involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the development of a complete system for on-board MAV planning.
